@AuthService_HostAddress = http://localhost:5101
@ApiGateway = http://localhost:5100

### 1. Health Check
GET {{AuthService_HostAddress}}/health
Accept: application/json

### 2. Sprawdź wymogi haseł
GET {{AuthService_HostAddress}}/api/auth/password-requirements
Accept: application/json

### 3. Rejestracja nowego użytkownika (Customer)
POST {{AuthService_HostAddress}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jan.kowalski@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "firstName": "Jan",
  "lastName": "Kowalski",
  "phoneNumber": "+48123456789"
}

### 4. Logowanie
POST {{AuthService_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jan.kowalski@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 5. Refresh Token (użyj refreshToken z odpowiedzi logowania)
POST {{AuthService_HostAddress}}/api/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### 6. Logout
POST {{AuthService_HostAddress}}/api/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

### 7. Przez API Gateway - Rejestracja
POST {{ApiGateway}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "anna.nowak@example.com",
  "password": "password456",
  "firstName": "Anna",
  "lastName": "Nowak",
  "phoneNumber": "+48987654321"
}

### 8. Przez API Gateway - Logowanie
POST {{ApiGateway}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "anna.nowak@example.com",
  "password": "password456"
}

### 9. Przez API Gateway - Wymogi haseł
GET {{ApiGateway}}/api/auth/password-requirements
Accept: application/json
